    • search

      This method searches for a certain key.
      Parameters:
      root - the root of tree
      key - the key to search for.
      Returns:
      the position of the node of the key if it exists.

    • findInRange

      void findInRange​(int root, int kMin, int kMax)
      This method finds the keys between a certain range [kMin, kMax].
      Parameters:
      root - root of tree
      kMin - the left limit of the range.
      kMax - the right limit of the range.

    • randomSearches

      void randomSearches​(int numOfSearches)
      This method generates a random array of integers to search for, then searches them by calling the function "search".
      Parameters:
      numOfSearches - an integer that indicates how many integers will be searched in the Threaded Binary Search Tree.

    • rangeRandomSearching

      void rangeRandomSearching​(int range, int numOfSearches)
      This method generates a random integer, then creates the range the user asked for and finally calls "findInRange" method to search within this range.
      Parameters:
      range - an integer that indicates the range to search within
      numOfSearches - an integer that indicates the number of searches to be executed
